        <h3>Mo Ryan - <i>Defensive Assistant Coordinator</i></h3>
        <p>
          Mo Ryan is a new addition to the Stanford Men's Lacrosse Program as
          well as the West Coast.  A New Jersey native, Mo Played lacrosse at
          St. Peter's Prep ('01) and later moved onto Marquette University
          ('05) serving as each team's captain from Jr. year on. Since
          graduating, Mo has held coaching positions ranging from Defensive
          Co-ordinator to Head Coach and been to two NJ state championship
          games, winning in 2008 with Morristown Beard.  An active scout, Mo
          looks forward to helping Stanford both on and off the field.
        </p>
